sec.p:
A total of k = 7 studies were included in the analysis (in bold in Table 3; Fig. 5)20,21,39–41,45,48. The observed standardized mean differences ranged from − 1.13 to − 0.01, with all estimates being negative (100%). The estimated average standardized mean difference (i.e., Glass’s estimator obtained with metafor::escalc()) based on the random-effects model was \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
